      <section eId="sec_15_1301">
        <num>15-1301</num>
        <heading>Definitions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_15_1301__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>in a county, the county legislative\nbody;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_15_1301__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>in a city, the board of aldermen, common council, commission\nor other body vested by its charter or other law with jurisdiction to\nenact ordinances or local laws, except that in a city having a\npopulation of one million or more, if there be a board of estimate, the\nterm "governing body" shall mean such board of estimate;</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_15_1301__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>in a town,\nthe town board; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_15_1301__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>in a village, the board of trustees.\n  5. "Local agency" means the department, bureau, commission, board,\ndivision, agency, public benefit corporation, administration, or\ncommittee of municipalities, designated by the governing body of each\nparticipating municipality, or designated by the county legislative body\nin the case of a county acting on its own motion, to conduct and develop\ncomprehensive studies and reports.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
